latestPosts.caption:
First ever official race done. I’m not an endurance runner by nature, more of a sprinter but after years of lifting i decided to give running a shot. 4 months later, I crossed the finish line!!!
 Knee pain tried to hold me back (7k in and it was brutal 😅), but a little massage and spray got me through. The goal was to do it under 46 minutes, but progress takes time, and we’ll crush it soon.
 Huge shoutout to my boys for keeping the energy high and pushing each other to the finish line. 🙌 Next up? Half Marathon, here we come. #RaceDay #Endurance #RunningJourney #HalfMarathonSoon #ProgressNotPerfection #PushingLimits
